**Verdict: REQUEST_CHANGES** — 3 findings across the new store actions.

**Finding 1 (HIGH) — `continueInChat`: seed-message calls are fire-and-forget**
`frontend/src/store.ts:965-975` — The two `apiFetch` calls that inject the system (briefing context) and assistant opening messages don't check `res.ok`. A 4xx/5xx response resolves normally, execution continues, and the user lands in an empty chat with no error. Fix: add `if (!res.ok) throw new Error(...)` after each — the same pattern already used one line above for the session creation call.

**Finding 2 (MEDIUM) — `switchSession`: failure leaves stale session with no user feedback**
`frontend/src/store.ts:947-952` — Both the `else` branch and the `catch` only reset `historyLoading`. No error state is set, `sessionId` remains pointing to the new session, and the function doesn't rethrow — so when called from `continueInChat`, failure is fully swallowed: user navigates to chat and sees an empty panel. Fix: add `set({ error: ... })` to both failure paths.

**Finding 3 (LOW) — `fetchSessions`: broad silent catch**
`frontend/src/store.ts:932-934` — `catch { // ignore }` with no logging. Inconsistent with `fetchNudges` (`// best-effort`). If this fails after `continueInChat`, the origin badge never appears. Fix: update comment to `// best-effort` at minimum; optionally add `console.warn`.
