## Code Review: PR #716 — REQUEST_CHANGES

**3 findings** across 10 files reviewed.

### CRITICAL — System messages visible in chat UI
**Location**: `ChatPanel.tsx:1015`, `schemas.ts:76`

`continueInChat` stores the briefing context as `role: 'system'`, but `messages.map(msg => <MessageBubble />)` renders every message without filtering. Since `isUser = msg.role === 'user'` (false for `system`), the full raw briefing text renders as a Reli assistant bubble — the user sees the prompt-engineering text before the intended opening message.

Secondary: `ChatMessageSchema` only allows `['user', 'assistant']`, so the system message triggers a console warning on every `switchSession` call.

**Fix**: Two lines — filter `role === 'system'` before the render map, and add `'system'` to the Zod enum.

### HIGH — `fetchSessions` never called on app init
**Location**: `App.tsx:66-98`, `store.ts:927`

`fetchSessions` is implemented but not wired into the `useEffect` that fires on login. `sessions` initialises to `[]` and stays there after page reload, so `currentSession` is always `undefined` in ChatPanel — the "Briefing"/"Weekly" badges and session title never show after a refresh.

**Fix**: Add `fetchSessions()` to the App.tsx init `useEffect` alongside `fetchThings`, `fetchBriefing`, etc.

### LOW — `sessionId: null` in test mock contradicts store type
**Location**: `ChatPanel.test.tsx:38`

The mock uses `null as string | null` but the store declares `sessionId: string`. Should be `''`.

**Positive**: Migration chain valid, serialiser field access correct, session endpoints properly user-isolated, screenshots updated, role test update intentional and documented.
